  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The particle ×›Ö¼×™, \"for\" (Jehovah visited), does not mean if, as, or when, nor is it to be regarded as a copyist's error. It is only necessary to supply the thought contained in the words, \"Eli blessed Elkanah,\" viz., that Eli's blessing was not an empty fruitless wish; and to understand the passage in some such way as this: Eli's word was fulfilled, or still more simply, they went to their home blessed; for Jehovah visited Hannah, blessed her with \"three sons and two daughters; but the boy Samuel grew up with the Lord,\" i.e., near to Him (at the sanctuary), and under His protection and blessing. ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
